#dreambig #daretodream #chasewhatmatters #moto
Luckiest Man Alive

“I’d rather die young and live than live old and regret” 

I wrote this song about my passion for music, about pursuing that which is most important to me. Not for the money but because of how much it means to me. My grandfather and my father passed down to me a saying that I think about all of the time. “If you love what you do, you’ll never work a day in your life”. 

What are you most passionate about and how are you prioritizing that? Would love to hear about what drives you 💪

Follow me on Spotify and listen to ‘Money’ and more

This is one of the first songs where I recorded myself singing the chorus and didn’t hate it. 

I do it for the love. Not the money. Well, at first I did it to get the ladies 😍🕺🏻🤪

Sometimes I hide behind the walls, built to protect and guard against emotional pain, not realizing that I am also creating a major obstacle to emotional growth. Do you find yourself in a similar situation?

When I was writing this song, I thought about those moments I may have missed by maintaining the masks. Inspired by the desire to connect deeper. 

Add me and follow me on Spotify for more 🙏

https://open.spotify.com/artist/48HCfnsol6PGFXVlcHcpBR?si=TUrKSY93RaW6J52UrAAVYw

🎶💙 Much Love, Always B U 💙🎶

#LetMeIn #Connect #BreakDownYourWalls #VulnerabilityIsStrength

The thought of unveiling the true self, behind the masks we wear, inspired the line ‘Let me see the side your lies don’t show’. Getting to the true depth of someone, not just the faces we put out for people to see, but the ones we hold private. True vulnerability. It’s a difficult ask but it’s the heart of a deeper connection once it’s beauty is established. 

#LetMeIn #Vulnerability #DeeperMeaning #Real

I have been at this for a long time. The delivery has definitely changed, the passion and drive has not. It’s a tough gig to pursue and often times feels insurmountable. I haven’t nearly achieved the success I predicted for myself, yet, but I have enjoyed the journey. I look at these numbers and am extremely grateful for all of you that have listened, liked, shared and been a part of this journey with me. I also see these numbers as an opportunity to be better. To be more consistent, to push myself harder, to share more and embrace how things have changed. I have much loftier goals, so for 2024 I hope that you will all continue to show your support by following, listening, liking and sharing. It means the world to me. Thank you for being a part of me. 🙏💙 Much Love
